3.00	Animal_coloration	Animal coloration	Animal coloration is the general appearance of an animal resulting from the reflection or emission of light from its surfaces. The mechanisms for colour production in animals include pigments, chromatophores, structural coloration, and bioluminescence.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4b/Orientalischer_S%C3%BC%C3%9Flippfisch.jpg/400px-Orientalischer_S%C3%BC%C3%9Flippfisch.jpg
